<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4002: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-30T23:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                        1926—11 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 31—12:48
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>66. My telegram No. 65, October 29, 5 p.m. President Paz has just sent
                            the Minister of Foreign Affairs and the Minister of War to inform me
                            that in view of the unusual conditions existing at Ceiba the carrying
                            out of his orders [cannot be effected?], however I am informed that
                            Minister of War will be sent at once to Ceiba. Repeated to Ceiba.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>